cs.CV, cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.NE

The paper involves the use of deep learning and image analysis techniques to transform unlabelled tissue autofluorescence images into histologically stained versions. This falls under the domain of computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE). The paper also involves the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image generation, which falls under the domain of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper involves the use of information retrieval techniques for comparing the virtual staining method with standard histological staining, which falls under the domain of information retrieval (cs.IR).
